The patient denied having a CT-A of the right coronary artery, which revealed a 2.3 x 1.3 mm stenosis in the right coronary artery.

A heart catheterization was performed, in which 70% of the left anterior descending artery (LAD) was evaluated and angina was found to be present as well as moderate severe myocardial ischemia.  The patient was treated with LAD angioplasty.  He was also evaluated for possible aortic valve regurgitation.  The patient denied the presence of aortic regurgitation, and denied a catheterization for further evaluation of the left atrium and valve regurgitation.

The patient had a stable CHF at 40 years of age.

The patient is now discharged from the hospital.  He will continue with monitoring at home, for which he has been receiving for 4 nights.  He will be discharged to the ICU with a daytime diabetic regimen.
